data.name: buttonHelp.ToolTip
data.value:
Presets are multistep case changing with new casing rules and/or excepted words/characters on every step.
You can record your own preset. First enumerate the excepted words/characters, then click the "Record preset" button. Select casing rule and choose enumerated excepted words/characters from DROPDOWN LIST if needed. Click the "Preview" button. Change the casing rule and/or select new or the same excepted words/characters from DROPDOWN LIST if needed. Click the "Reapply rules to new tag" button. Repeat this step as many times as required. Then click the "Stop recording" button. Name your preset.
